   <abstract xlink:href="http://lib.lsu.edu/services/oralhistory/abstracts/mckinley/2_businesses/Smith_Charles_T1041.pdf">Smith recalls African American-owned businesses in South Baton Rouge including
            restaurants, barber shops, grocery stores, beauty shops, drug stores, etc. He explains
            how African American-owned businesses could not compete with white businesses following
            integration and how many were forced to close. He describes a typical day in the
            neighborhood and how the African American church is a success story among minority-owned
            businesses.</abstract>
